\details{
FUNDEB (Fundo de Manutencao e Desenvolvimento da Educacao Basica e de
Valorizacao dos Profissionais da Educacao) is the main funding mechanism
for basic education in Brazil.

Each Excel file from STN contains ~20 data sheets named with a prefix
indicating the destination (\code{E_} for states, \code{M_} for municipalities)
and a suffix indicating the funding source (e.g., \code{E_FPE}, \code{M_ICMS}).
Each sheet contains two tables: the main FUNDEB transfers and a
FUNDEB adjustment table.

\strong{Important notes:}
\itemize{
\item Data is sourced from STN (Tesouro Nacional), not INEP.
\item Files are in Excel format (XLS) — requires the \code{readxl} package.
\item Column names are standardized to lowercase with underscores.
\item Summary sheets (Resumo, Total, etc.) are automatically excluded.
}
